# Business Rules Documentation
## CareWell Health Services - Patient Appointment & Care Management System

---

## 1. Patient Management Rules

### 1.1 Patient Registration
- **Rule P1**: All patients must provide a valid email address
  - Format: standard email format (user@domain.com)
  - Unique: No duplicate emails allowed
  
- **Rule P2**: Patient phone number is required
  - Format: Any numeric string, minimum 10 digits
  - Used for appointment notifications

- **Rule P3**: Date of birth is mandatory
  - Must be a valid date
  - Patient must be at least 0 years old (born today or earlier)
  - Cannot be a future date

- **Rule P4**: Each patient receives a unique system-generated ID
  - Format: PAT + timestamp + random string

### 1.2 Patient Status
- **Rule P5**: Patients can be marked as Active or Inactive
- **Rule P6**: Inactive patients cannot schedule new appointments
- **Rule P7**: Patient history remains accessible even when inactive

---

## 2. Appointment Scheduling Rules

### 2.1 Double Booking Prevention
- **Rule A1**: A doctor cannot have two appointments at the same date/time
  - Check: Same doctor + overlapping time slots
  - Exception: If either appointment is cancelled or marked NoShow

- **Rule A2**: Appointment times must be in the future
  - Cannot schedule appointments in the past
  - Minimum: Current time + 15 minutes

### 2.2 Appointment Duration
- **Rule A3**: Default appointment duration is 30 minutes
- **Rule A4**: Specialist consultations may be scheduled for 45-60 minutes

### 2.3 Scheduling Window
- **Rule A5**: Appointments can be scheduled up to 90 days in advance
- **Rule A6**: Same-day appointments allowed with availability check

---

## 3. Appointment Status Rules

### 3.1 Valid Statuses
| Status | Description | Terminal State |
|--------|-------------|----------------|
| Scheduled | Newly created appointment | No |
| Confirmed | Patient confirmed attendance | No |
| InProgress | Patient checked in, waiting for doctor | No |
| Completed | Consultation finished | Yes |
| Cancelled | Appointment cancelled by staff/patient | Yes |
| NoShow | Patient did not arrive | Yes |

### 3.2 Status Transitions
- **Rule S1**: Scheduled → Confirmed (manual or automated)
- **Rule S2**: Confirmed → InProgress (patient check-in)
- **Rule S3**: InProgress → Completed (after consultation)
- **Rule S4**: Scheduled/Confirmed → Cancelled (before appointment time)
- **Rule S5**: Scheduled/Confirmed → NoShow (past appointment time, patient absent)

### 3.3 Status Transition Validation
- **Rule S6**: Cannot change status from a terminal state (Completed, Cancelled, NoShow)
- **Rule S7**: Cannot mark as NoShow before appointment time has passed

---

## 4. Cancellation Rules

### 4.1 Cancellation Timeframe
- **Rule C1**: Appointments can be cancelled up to 2 hours before scheduled time
- **Rule C2**: Emergency cancellations allowed at any time with reason

### 4.2 Cancellation Reasons
- **Rule C3**: Cancellation reason is mandatory
- **Rule C4**: Common reasons: Patient request, Doctor unavailable, Administrative

---

## 5. Doctor Management Rules

### 5.1 Availability
- **Rule D1**: Doctors can be marked as Available or Unavailable
- **Rule D2**: Unavailable doctors cannot receive new appointments

### 5.2 Department Assignment
- **Rule D3**: Each doctor belongs to one department
- **Rule D4**: Doctors can only take appointments for their specialty

---

## 6. Reporting Rules

### 6.1 No-Show Calculation
- **Rule R1**: No-Show = Appointments with status 'NoShow'
- **Rule R2**: No-Show Rate = (NoShows / Total Appointments) × 100

### 6.2 Utilization Calculation
- **Rule R3**: Utilization Rate = (Completed / Total Scheduled) × 100
- **Rule R4**: Excludes cancelled appointments from calculation

### 6.3 Date Ranges
- **Rule R5**: Default report period is last 30 days
- **Rule R6**: Maximum report period is 365 days

---

## 7. Validation Rules Summary

| Field | Required | Format | Validation |
|-------|----------|--------|------------|
| Patient Name | Yes | String | Min 2 chars, Max 100 |
| Patient Email | Yes | Email | Valid format, unique |
| Patient Phone | Yes | String | Min 10 digits |
| Patient DOB | Yes | Date | Not future, valid date |
| Appointment Date | Yes | DateTime | Future only |
| Appointment Reason | Yes | String | Min 5 chars |
| Doctor | Yes | ID | Must exist, be available |

---

## 8. Error Messages

| Error Type | Message | Resolution |
|------------|---------|-------------|
| Double Booking | "Doctor already has an appointment at this time" | Choose different time/doctor |
| Invalid Status | "Invalid status transition from {current} to {target}" | Check valid transitions |
| Patient Inactive | "Patient is not eligible for scheduling" | Reactivate patient first |
| Past Date | "Appointment cannot be scheduled in the past" | Choose future date |
| Required Field | "{Field} is required" | Fill in required fields |

